 revisionDate) {\n   108→        this.revisionDate = revisionDate;\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @Column(table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\")\n   112→    @Lob\n   113→    public Serializable getDrawing() {\n   114→        return drawing;\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    public void setDrawing(Serializable drawing) {\n   118→        this.drawing = drawing;\n   119→    }\n   120→\n   121→    @Column(table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\")\n   122→    @Lob\n   123→    public String getSpecification() {\n   124→        return specification;\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public void setSpecification(String specification) {\n   128→        this.specification = specification;\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    @ManyToOne\n   132→    @JoinColumns({\n   133→        @JoinColumn(name=\"BOMPARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName=\"PARTNUMBER\"),\n   134→        @JoinColumn(name=\"BOMREVISION\", referencedColumnName=\"REVISION\")\n   135→    })\n   136→    public Part getBomPart() {\n   137→        return bomPart;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public void setBomPart(Part bomPart) {\n   141→        this.bomPart = bomPart;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    @OneToMany(mappedBy=\"bomPart\")\n   145→    public List<Part> getParts() {\n   146→        return parts;\n   147→    }\n   148→\n   149→    public void setParts(List<Part> parts) {\n   150→        this.parts = parts;\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    @OneToOne(mappedBy=\"part\")\n   154→    public VendorPart getVendorPart() {\n   155→        return vendorPart;\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    public void setVendorPart(VendorPart vendorPart) {\n   159→        this.vendorPart = vendorPart;\n   160→    }\n   161→}\n   162→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer ques