{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01KboswRHQ4duXUCrjrPKXH6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CSS returns empty. This is because static resources under `/css/` are being intercepted by the JAX-RS `@Path(\"/\")` application root. With Open Liberty, static files should be in the `webapp` directory. The JAX-RS application path is `/` so it catches everything. I need to either change the app path or add a static file servlet. Since the CSS is in `webapp/css/default.css`, it should be served by the servlet container. The issue is likely that the JAX-RS application at `@Path(\"/\")` is catching the request. Let me check:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":398,"cache_read_input_tokens":132961,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":398,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":225},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"a4ccc76a-4f78-44f8-abe2-46ddce918b74"}
