{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LyfuGtGf7YKmgnBVEvb8Eu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is `NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \"jakarta.persistence.EntityManager.persist(java.lang.Object)\" because \"this.em\" is null`. This is happening in the `StartupInitializer` during CDI `@Initialized(ApplicationScoped.class)`. The `@PersistenceContext` injection isn't working at that point because the JPA subsystem hasn't fully initialized yet when the CDI application scope is initialized.\n\nThe problem is that `@Initialized(ApplicationScoped.class)` fires too early. Let me change the initialization approach. I'll use a `@Startup` EJB singleton instead, or use a `ServletContextListener`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1146,"cache_read_input_tokens":138441,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1146,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":269},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"24ba6a16-fbbd-40b6-8612-4d2005b28988"}
