{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WFzqm6ySwKeRSu3r11nHmf","type":"tool_result","content":"jakarta.ejb.NoSuchEJBException: An error occurred during initialization of singleton session bean order-jakarta#order-jakarta.war#StartupInitializer, resulting in the discarding of the singleton instance.; nested exception is: jakarta.ejb.EJBTransactionRolledbackException: setRollbackOnly called from within a singleton post construct method.\n\tat com.ibm.ejs.container.util.ExceptionUtil.NoSuchEJBException(ExceptionUtil.java:433)\n\tat [internal classes]\nCaused by: jakarta.ejb.EJBTransactionRolledbackException: setRollbackOnly called from within a singleton post construct method.\n\tat com.ibm.ejs.container.EJSContainer.postInvokeForLifecycleInterceptors(EJSContainer.java:4216)\n\t... 1 more\n\n[ERROR   ] CNTR4002E: The order-jakarta.war EJB module in the order-jakarta application failed to start. Exception: com.ibm.ws.exception.RuntimeWarning: CNTR0201E: The StartupInitializer startup singleton session bean in the order-jakarta.war module failed initialization.\n\tat com.ibm.ejs.csi.EJBApplicationMetaData.createStartupBeans(EJBApplicationMetaData.java:1016)\n\tat [internal classes]\nCaused by: jakarta.ejb.NoSuchEJBException: An error occurred during initialization of singleton session bean order-jakarta#order-jakarta.war#StartupInitializer, resulting in the discarding of the singleton instance.; nested exception is: jakarta.ejb.EJBTransactionRolledbackException: setRollbackOnly called from within a singleton post construct method.\n\tat com.ibm.ejs.container.util.ExceptionUtil.NoSuchEJBException(ExceptionUtil.java:433)\n\t... 1 more\nCaused by: jakarta.ejb.EJBTransactionRolledbackException: setRollbackOnly called from within a singleton post construct method.\n\tat com.ibm.ejs.container.EJSContainer.postInvokeForLifecycleInterceptors(EJSContainer.java:4216)\n\t... 1 more\n\n[ERROR   ] CWWKZ0002E: An exception occurred while starting the application order-jakarta. The exception message was: com.ibm.ws.container.service.state.StateChangeException: com.ibm.ws.exception.RuntimeWarning: CNTR0201E: The StartupInitializer startup singleton session bean in the order-jakarta.war module failed initialization.\n[AUDIT   ] CWWKF0012I: The server installed the following features: [appAuthentication-3.0, appSecurity-5.0, beanValidation-3.0, cdi-4.0, concurrent-3.0, distributedMap-1.0, enterpriseBeansLite-4.0, expressionLanguage-5.0, faces-4.0, jdbc-4.2, jndi-1.0, jsonb-3.0, jsonp-2.1, managedBeans-2.0, pages-3.1, persistence-3.1, persistenceContainer-3.1, restfulWS-3.1, restfulWSClient-3.1, servlet-6.0, ssl-1.0, transportSecurity-1.0, webProfile-10.0, websocket-2.1].\n[AUDIT   ] CWWKF0011I: The defaultServer server is ready to run a smarter planet. The defaultServer server started in 3.876 seconds.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"b8116a21-eda7-4d85-bda7-9eaec46fea16"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DGKfHDwtnVQ8BZkGrw3prV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is that `setRollbackOnly` is being called during the `@PostConstruct` of a singleton. This happens because the `@Transactional` annotation on `createData()` (or the repository methods) is calling `setRollbackOnly` during the container-managed transaction. With EJB `@Singleton`, the `@PostConstruct` method runs in a transaction context, and calling methods with `@Transactional` causes issues because they try to manage their own transactions.\n\nThe fix is to not use `@Transactional` on the `OrderConfigService.createData()` method and to make sure the repositories' `@Transactional` works within the EJB's CMT. Actually, the issue is different - with EJB singletons, the container manages the transaction, and the `@Transactional` (CDI interceptor) on the repository methods conflicts with the CMT.\n\nI should use a `@TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)` on the EJB or use `@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.BEAN)` to avoid the conflict. But the simpler approach is to use a `ServletContextListener`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":974,"cache_read_input_tokens":142501,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":974,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":621},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"68e42964-4481-48e2-89ad-417965a47330"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DGKfHDwtnVQ8BZkGrw3prV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_011cyMLWNbunRwMSmo7R2dJW","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__order__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/jakarta/tutorial/order/web/StartupInitializer.java","content":"package jakarta.tutorial.order.web;\n\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.servlet.ServletContextEvent;\nimport jakarta.servlet.ServletContextListener;\nimport jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebListener;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.tutorial.order.service.OrderConfigService;\n\n@WebListener\npublic class StartupInitializer implements ServletContextListener {\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(StartupInitializer.class.getName());\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderConfigService orderConfigService;\n\n    @Override\n    public void contextInitialized(ServletContextEvent sce) {\n        logger.info(\"Manually triggering dataset initialization\");\n        orderConfigService.createData();\n        logger.info(\"Manual dataset initialization completed\");\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void contextDestroyed(ServletContextEvent sce) {\n        // cleanup if needed\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":974,"cache_read_input_tokens":142501,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":974,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":621},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"bb4fdaf6-7c65-4287-a92d-864893866be8"}
