{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_015xWrBqoW8igSh9uEJTVnzZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The same error - `EntityManager` is null. The `@PersistenceContext` injection isn't happening in the CDI-managed repository beans. This is likely because in Open Liberty, `@PersistenceContext` injection needs the beans to be EJBs or use specific CDI producers, or the persistence unit name needs to match.\n\nWait - the `persistence.xml` uses `orderPU` but the `@PersistenceContext(unitName = \"orderPU\")` is in the repositories. But look at the first successful run - it worked! The difference was in the first run, the WAR name was `order-jakarta` and the persistence unit was matched. Let me check the full log to see if there's a JPA error BEFORE the NPE:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1367,"cache_read_input_tokens":145464,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1367,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":297},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"35f3bcaf-b060-4abd-b958-b10d2b4501ae"}
