{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_017B9TC2GXPGAoVKKktJb5W6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me look at the first successful run more carefully. In that run, the server started correctly and H2 connected. But what was different? In that first run, the server.xml had `properties.h2.embedded` with the URL. But then when I rebuilt, it broke. Let me check if the issue is timing - maybe the `properties.h2.embedded` attribute name is not recognized. \n\nThe proper way for Open Liberty with a custom JDBC driver is to use the `properties` element (for generic JDBC) but define the `databaseName` attribute. With H2, the connection URL should be set through the H2 DataSource class. Let me try a different approach - use the H2 DataSource class directly:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":233,"cache_read_input_tokens":149038,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":233,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":268},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"24ded87d-460a-4b8f-9fff-ec734588b7a5"}
