{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JkUPGnyXPXfLnS7TsWsLJF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server description=\"Order Jakarta Application\">\n     2→\n     3→    <featureManager>\n     4→        <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     5→    </featureManager>\n     6→\n     7→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\"\n     8→                  httpPort=\"${default.http.port}\"\n     9→                  httpsPort=\"9443\"/>\n    10→\n    11→    <!-- H2 JDBC library -->\n    12→    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n    13→        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2-*.jar\"/>\n    14→    </library>\n    15→\n    16→    <!-- DataSource configuration using H2 in-memory -->\n    17→    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/orderDS\">\n    18→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    19→        <properties.h2.embedded\n    20→            databaseName=\"order\"\n    21→            URL=\"jdbc:h2:mem:order;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n    22→            user=\"sa\"\n    23→            password=\"\"/>\n    24→    </dataSource>\n    25→\n    26→    <!-- Application configuration -->\n    27→    <webApplication location=\"order-jakarta.war\" contextRoot=\"/\">\n    28→        <classloader commonLibraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    29→    </webApplication>\n    30→\n    31→</server>\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"39781c46-008f-4335-a23d-81f2372f7965"}
