{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015FxTGR6A4zvEs7zgxLMhdA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns:th=\"http://www.thymeleaf.org\">\n     3→<head>\n     4→    <title>Order Java Persistence Example</title>\n     5→    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/default.css\"/>\n     6→</head>\n     7→<body>\n     8→    <h1>Order Java Persistence Example</h1>\n     9→\n    10→    <h2>View All Orders</h2>\n    11→    <table rules=\"all\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n    12→        <tr>\n    13→            <th>Order ID</th>\n    14→            <th>Shipment Info</th>\n    15→            <th>Status</th>\n    16→            <th>Last Updated</th>\n    17→            <th>Discount</th>\n    18→            <th>Actions</th>\n    19→        </tr>\n    20→        <tr th:each=\"order : ${orders}\">\n    21→            <td>\n    22→                <a th:href=\"@{/lineItems(orderId=${order.orderId})}\" th:text=\"${order.orderId}\"></a>\n    23→            </td>\n    24→            <td th:text=\"${order.shipmentInfo}\"></td>\n    25→            <td th:text=\"${order.status}\"></td>\n    26→            <td th:text=\"${order.lastUpdate}\"></td>\n    27→            <td><span th:text=\"${order.discount}\"></span>%</td>\n    28→            <td>\n    29→                <form method=\"post\" action=\"/removeOrder\">\n    30→                    <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"orderId\" th:value=\"${order.orderId}\"/>\n    31→                    <button type=\"submit\">Delete</button>\n    32→                </form>\n    33→            </td>\n    34→        </tr>\n    35→    </table>\n    36→\n    37→    <h2>Create New Order</h2>\n    38→    <form method=\"post\" action=\"/submitOrder\">\n    39→        <label for=\"orderIdInputText\">Order ID: </label>\n    40→        <input type=\"number\" id=\"orderIdInputText\" name=\"newOrderId\" required/><br/>\n    41→        <label for=\"shipmentInfoInputText\">Shipment Info: </label>\n    42→        <input type=\"text\" id=\"shipmentInfoInputText\" name=\"newOrderShippingInfo\" required/><br/>\n    43→        <label for=\"statusMenu\">Status: </label>\n    44→        <select id=\"statusMenu\" name=\"newOrderStatus\" required>\n    45→            <option value=\"Y\">Complete</option>\n    46→            <option value=\"N\">Pending</option>\n    47→        </select><br/>\n    48→        <label for=\"discountMenu\">Discount: </label>\n    49→        <select id=\"discountMenu\" name=\"newOrderDiscount\" required>\n    50→            <option value=\"0\">0 %</option>\n    51→            <option value=\"5\">5 %</option>\n    52→            <option value=\"10\">10 %</option>\n    53→            <option value=\"15\">15 %</option>\n    54→            <option value=\"20\">20 %</option>\n    55→            <option value=\"25\">25 %</option>\n    56→            <option value=\"30\">30 %</option>\n    57→            <option value=\"35\">35 %</option>\n    58→            <option value=\"40\">40 %</option>\n    59→        </select><br/>\n    60→        <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n    61→    </form>\n    62→\n    63→    <h2>Find Vendors</h2>\n    64→    <form method=\"post\" action=\"/findVendor\">\n    65→        <label for=\"findVendorInputText\">Search for Vendors: </label>\n    66→        <input type=\"text\" id=\"findVendorInputText\" name=\"vendorName\" th:value=\"${vendorName}\" required/>\n    67→        <button type=\"submit\" id=\"findVendorButton\">Find Vendor</button>\n    68→    </form>\n    69→\n    70→    <div th:if=\"${findVendorTableDisabled}\">\n    71→        <table rules=\"all\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n    72→            <tr><th>Vendor</th></tr>\n    73→            <tr th:each=\"vendor : ${vendorSearchResults}\">\n    74→                <td th:text=\"${vendor}\"></td>\n    75→            </tr>\n    76→        </table>\n    77→    </div>\n    78→</body>\n    79→</html>\n    80→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"7f47ed0c-9329-4b5d-9eba-43fb2d0299a8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013Z3wDHNnKJAkT4gjnbsp57","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns:th=\"http://www.thymeleaf.org\">\n     3→<head>\n     4→    <title>Line Items for Order <span th:text=\"${currentOrder}\"></span></title>\n     5→    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/default.css\"/>\n     6→</head>\n     7→<body>\n     8→    <h1>Line Items for Order <span th:text=\"${currentOrder}\"></span></h1>\n     9→\n    10→    <form method=\"post\">\n    11→        <table rules=\"all\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n    12→            <tr>\n    13→                <th>Item ID</th>\n    14→                <th>Quantity</th>\n    15→                <th>Vendor Part Number</th>\n    16→            </tr>\n    17→            <tr th:each=\"lineItem : ${lineItems}\">\n    18→                <td th:text=\"${lineItem.itemId}\"></td>\n    19→                <td th:text=\"${lineItem.quantity}\"></td>\n    20→                <td th:text=\"${lineItem.vendorPart != null ? lineItem.vendorPart.vendorPartNumber : 'N/A'}\"></td>\n    21→            </tr>\n    22→        </table>\n    23→        <br/>\n    24→        <table id=\"orderPartsTable\" rules=\"all\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n    25→            <tr>\n    26→                <th>Part Number</th>\n    27→                <th>Revision</th>\n    28→                <th>Vendor Part Number</th>\n    29→                <th>Add To Order</th>\n    30→            </tr>\n    31→            <tr th:each=\"part : ${newOrderParts}\">\n    32→                <td th:text=\"${part.partNumber}\"></td>\n    33→                <td th:text=\"${part.revision}\"></td>\n    34→                <td th:text=\"${part.vendorPart != null ? part.vendorPart.vendorPartNumber : 'N/A'}\"></td>\n    35→                <td>\n    36→                    <form method=\"post\" action=\"/addLineItem\">\n    37→                        <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"currentOrder\" th:value=\"${currentOrder}\"/>\n    38→                        <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"selectedPartNumber\" th:value=\"${part.partNumber}\"/>\n    39→                        <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"selectedPartRevision\" th:value=\"${part.revision}\"/>\n    40→                        <button type=\"submit\">Add</button>\n    41→                    </form>\n    42→                </td>\n    43→            </tr>\n    44→        </table>\n    45→        <br/>\n    46→        <a href=\"/orders\">Back to Orders</a>\n    47→    </form>\n    48→</body>\n    49→</html>\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"6b30f4d4-7393-4205-879c-3b0285e02b8c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EaY1huw2gKsnSDqAjYdfiQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakarta.tutorial.order.web;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     6→import java.util.HashMap;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.Map;\n     9→\n    10→@Path(\"/\")\n    11→public class OrderWebController {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    OrderController orderController;\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    ThymeleafEngine thymeleaf;\n    18→\n    19→    @GET\n    20→    @Path(\"/orders\")\n    21→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    22→    public String getOrders(@QueryParam(\"vendorName\") String vendorName,\n    23→                            @QueryParam(\"vendorSearchResults\") List<String> vendorSearchResults) {\n    24→        Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();\n    25→        data.put(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders());\n    26→        data.put(\"vendorName\", vendorName);\n    27→        data.put(\"vendorSearchResults\", vendorSearchResults);\n    28→        data.put(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", vendorSearchResults != null && !vendorSearchResults.isEmpty());\n    29→        return thymeleaf.render(\"orders\", data);\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @POST\n    33→    @Path(\"/submitOrder\")\n    34→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    35→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    36→    public String submitOrder(\n    37→            @FormParam(\"newOrderId\") Integer newOrderId,\n    38→            @FormParam(\"newOrderStatus\") String newOrderStatus,\n    39→            @FormParam(\"newOrderDiscount\") int newOrderDiscount,\n    40→            @FormParam(\"newOrderShippingInfo\") String newOrderShippingInfo) {\n    41→        orderController.submitOrder(newOrderId, newOrderStatus.charAt(0), newOrderDiscount, newOrderShippingInfo);\n    42→        Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();\n    43→        data.put(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders());\n    44→        data.put(\"vendorName\", null);\n    45→        data.put(\"vendorSearchResults\", null);\n    46→        data.put(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", false);\n    47→        return thymeleaf.render(\"orders\", data);\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @POST\n    51→    @Path(\"/removeOrder\")\n    52→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    53→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    54→    public String removeOrder(@FormParam(\"orderId\") Integer orderId) {\n    55→        orderController.removeOrder(orderId);\n    56→        Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();\n    57→        data.put(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders());\n    58→        data.put(\"vendorName\", null);\n    59→        data.put(\"vendorSearchResults\", null);\n    60→        data.put(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", false);\n    61→        return thymeleaf.render(\"orders\", data);\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @GET\n    65→    @Path(\"/lineItems\")\n    66→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    67→    public String getLineItems(@QueryParam(\"orderId\") Integer orderId) {\n    68→        Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();\n    69→        data.put(\"currentOrder\", orderId);\n    70→        data.put(\"lineItems\", orderController.getLineItems(orderId));\n    71→        data.put(\"newOrderParts\", orderController.getNewOrderParts());\n    72→        return thymeleaf.render(\"lineItems\", data);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    @POST\n    76→    @Path(\"/addLineItem\")\n    77→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    78→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    79→    public String addLineItem(\n    80→            @FormParam(\"currentOrder\") Integer currentOrder,\n    81→            @FormParam(\"selectedPartNumber\") String selectedPartNumber,\n    82→            @FormParam(\"selectedPartRevision\") int selectedPartRevision) {\n    83→        orderController.addLineItem(currentOrder, selectedPartNumber, selectedPartRevision);\n    84→        Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();\n    85→        data.put(\"currentOrder\", currentOrder);\n    86→        data.put(\"lineItems\", orderController.getLineItems(currentOrder));\n    87→        data.put(\"newOrderParts\", orderController.getNewOrderParts());\n    88→        return thymeleaf.render(\"lineItems\", data);\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    @POST\n    92→    @Path(\"/findVendor\")\n    93→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    94→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    95→    public String findVendor(@FormParam(\"vendorName\") String vendorName) {\n    96→        Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();\n    97→        data.put(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders());\n    98→        data.put(\"vendorName\", vendorName);\n    99→        data.put(\"vendorSearchResults\", orderController.findVendor(vendorName));\n   100→        data.put(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", true);\n   101→        return thymeleaf.render(\"orders\", data);\n   102→    }\n   103→}\n   104→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"1a40a782-9f31-46e9-9b4f-80aa828a3110"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_018RwhTRdJULEtUVmyeWKJMv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The template is located at `src/main/resources/templates/orders.html`. The Thymeleaf engine is configured with `resolver.setPrefix(\"templates/\")`, so when we call `render(\"orders\", data)`, it looks for `templates/orders.html` in the classpath. Let me check the ThymeleafEngine and also examine the WAR structure to see if the templates are actually at the right location:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4350,"cache_read_input_tokens":34734,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4350,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":291},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"4bacc772-c469-4023-a3a7-2ae8bd17cef5"}
