{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Pf1DPB8r1otodgDMBnzECe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakarta.tutorial.order.web;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import org.thymeleaf.TemplateEngine;\n     6→import org.thymeleaf.context.Context;\n     7→import org.thymeleaf.templatemode.TemplateMode;\n     8→import org.thymeleaf.templateresolver.ClassLoaderTemplateResolver;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.Map;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class ThymeleafEngine {\n    14→\n    15→    private TemplateEngine engine;\n    16→\n    17→    @PostConstruct\n    18→    public void init() {\n    19→        engine = new TemplateEngine();\n    20→        ClassLoaderTemplateResolver resolver = new ClassLoaderTemplateResolver();\n    21→        resolver.setPrefix(\"templates/\");\n    22→        resolver.setSuffix(\".html\");\n    23→        resolver.setTemplateMode(TemplateMode.HTML);\n    24→        resolver.setCharacterEncoding(\"UTF-8\");\n    25→        resolver.setCacheable(false);\n    26→        engine.setTemplateResolver(resolver);\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public String render(String templateName, Map<String, Object> variables) {\n    30→        Context ctx = new Context();\n    31→        if (variables != null) {\n    32→            ctx.setVariables(variables);\n    33→        }\n    34→        return engine.process(templateName, ctx);\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"0e9f9e84-bf8b-423f-bebf-93c513750fa8"}
