{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012gJLfwiqpVaPeTC9eqHuS7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem might be related to how the `ClassLoaderTemplateResolver` resolves templates in a WAR deployment on Liberty. The templates are in `src/main/resources/templates/` which puts them in `WEB-INF/classes/templates/` in the WAR. The `ClassLoaderTemplateResolver` uses the class loader, but in Liberty the webapp classloader might not have direct access to `WEB-INF/classes` via the thread context classloader the way we'd expect.\n\nLet me look more closely at the error. The error says \"An error happened during template parsing\" which means it IS finding the template but the parsing fails. This is a Thymeleaf parsing error, not a \"template not found\" error. Let me get better error details:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1238,"cache_read_input_tokens":39084,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1238,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":268},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"89ad5985-ad46-4cf5-991d-51e53f6bd91e"}
