{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VP9AzMjsdANY6CNec2SRuw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the actual error:\n\n```\nLink base \"/lineItems\" cannot be context relative (/...) unless the context used for \nexecuting the engine implements the org.thymeleaf.context.IWebContext interface\n```\n\nThe problem is that we're using `org.thymeleaf.context.Context` (non-web context) with `@{/lineItems(orderId=${order.orderId})}` link expressions. The `@{...}` syntax requires a web context (`IWebContext`) to resolve context-relative URLs. \n\nThere are two solutions:\n1. Replace `@{...}` link expressions in templates with plain `th:href` attribute expressions\n2. Use a `WebContext` instead of `Context`\n\nThe simplest fix is to replace the `@{...}` expressions with plain string concatenation in the templates:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1641,"cache_read_input_tokens":50644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1641,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":401},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"9c23f761-b451-4ce6-bb6c-f491cc6c9bf4"}
