{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01F1zpFa4u5L5hb9ckYdZ4Yr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good progress - the `@{...}` link issue is fixed but now there's a new error: `Accessing member 'getOrderId' is forbidden for type 'class jakarta.tutorial.order.entity.CustomerOrder' in this expression context.`\n\nThis is Thymeleaf's restricted OGNL expression evaluation. By default, Thymeleaf 3.1+ restricts access to certain members for security. Since we're using a non-web context (`Context` instead of `WebContext`), the restrictions are stricter.\n\nThe fix is to configure Thymeleaf to allow access to our entity classes. Let me update the ThymeleafEngine:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":669,"cache_read_input_tokens":55602,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":669,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":267},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"0e74d2ac-50e0-4abd-a7a7-86646d65b9db"}
