{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013vTBGzVqt58eeHfR3PLfVC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakarta.tutorial.order.service;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.tutorial.order.repository.CustomerOrderRepository;\n     4→import jakarta.tutorial.order.repository.LineItemRepository;\n     5→import jakarta.tutorial.order.repository.PartRepository;\n     6→import jakarta.tutorial.order.repository.VendorPartRepository;\n     7→import jakarta.tutorial.order.repository.VendorRepository;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class OrderConfigService {\n    15→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(OrderConfigService.class.getName());\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private PartRepository partRepository;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private VendorRepository vendorRepository;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private VendorPartRepository vendorPartRepository;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private CustomerOrderRepository customerOrderRepository;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private LineItemRepository lineItemRepository;\n    27→\n    28→    @Transactional\n    29→    public void createData() {\n    30→        logger.info(\"Starting dataset initialization\");\n    31→\n    32→        // Create Parts\n    33→        partRepository.createPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"ABC PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    34→        partRepository.createPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"DEF PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    35→        partRepository.createPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"GHI PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    36→        partRepository.createPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"XYZ PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    37→        partRepository.createPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"BOM PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    38→\n    39→        // Add Parts to BOM\n    40→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"1234-5678-01\", 1);\n    41→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"9876-4321-02\", 2);\n    42→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"5456-6789-03\", 3);\n    43→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5);\n    44→\n    45→        // Create Vendors\n    46→        vendorRepository.createVendor(100, \"WidgetCorp\", \"111 Main St., Anytown, KY 99999\", \"Mr. Jones\", \"888-777-9999\");\n    47→        vendorRepository.createVendor(200, \"Gadget, Inc.\", \"123 State St., Sometown, MI 88888\", \"Mrs. Smith\", \"866-345-6789\");\n    48→\n    49→        // Create VendorParts\n    50→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"PART1\", 100.00, 100);\n    51→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"PART2\", 10.44, 200);\n    52→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"PART3\", 76.23, 200);\n    53→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"PART4\", 55.19, 100);\n    54→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"PART5\", 345.87, 100);\n    55→\n    56→        // Create Orders and LineItems\n    57→        Integer orderId = 1111;\n    58→        customerOrderRepository.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 10, \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    59→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 3);\n    60→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"9876-4321-02\", 2, 5);\n    61→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 7);\n    62→\n    63→        orderId = 4312;\n    64→        customerOrderRepository.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 0, \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    65→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, 1);\n    66→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 3);\n    67→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 15);\n    68→\n    69→        logger.info(\"Order data initialization completed successfully\");\n    70→    }\n    71→}\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"39872ee6-4ae0-4666-af13-fc54aa08a2d2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011oQh1HWU8GQrooAULuKgwS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `@WebListener` approach with `@Inject` should work in Jakarta EE since CDI is integrated with Servlet container listeners. But the issue may be that Liberty's CDI integration with `@WebListener` doesn't inject beans when we also have JAX-RS `@ApplicationPath(\"/\")`. Let me change the approach - instead of using `@WebListener`, let me use a CDI `@Startup` bean with `@ApplicationScoped` and `@Initialized`:\n\nActually, let me try a different approach - use a simple CDI startup observer that's more reliable:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2123,"cache_read_input_tokens":75442,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2123,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":245},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"1fe5edbe-1fdf-47c2-b998-94c6b31b9da1"}
