{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018uc7ANnxEaJvt922DjGLPf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.order.entity;\n    13→\n    14→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    15→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    16→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n    17→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    18→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    19→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumns;\n    20→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    21→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    22→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.OneToOne;\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.UniqueConstraint;\n    27→\n    28→@Entity\n    29→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_VENDOR_PART\",\n    30→       uniqueConstraints=\n    31→           @UniqueConstraint(columnNames={\"PARTNUMBER\", \"PARTREVISION\"})\n    32→)\n    33→@NamedQueries({\n    34→    @NamedQuery(\n    35→        name=\"findAverageVendorPartPrice\",\n    36→        query=\"SELECT AVG(vp.price) \" +\n    37→              \"FROM VendorPart vp\"\n    38→    ),\n    39→    @NamedQuery(\n    40→        name=\"findTotalVendorPartPricePerVendor\",\n    41→        query=\"SELECT SUM(vp.price) \" +\n    42→              \"FROM VendorPart vp \" +\n    43→              \"WHERE vp.vendor.vendorId = :id\"\n    44→    ),\n    45→    @NamedQuery(\n    46→        name=\"findAllVendorParts\",\n    47→        query=\"SELECT vp FROM VendorPart vp ORDER BY vp.vendorPartNumber\"\n    48→    )\n    49→})\n    50→public class VendorPart implements java.io.Serializable {\n    51→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 4685631589912848921L;\n    52→    private Long vendorPartNumber;\n    53→    private String description;\n    54→    private double price;\n    55→    private Part part;\n    56→    private Vendor vendor;\n    57→\n    58→    public VendorPart() {}\n    59→\n    60→    public VendorPart(String description, double price, Part part) {\n    61→        this.description = description;\n    62→        this.price = price;\n    63→        this.part = part;\n    64→        part.setVendorPart(this);\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→\n    68→    @TableGenerator(\n    69→        name=\"vendorPartGen\",\n    70→        table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_SEQUENCE_GENERATOR\",\n    71→        pkColumnName=\"GEN_KEY\",\n    72→        valueColumnName=\"GEN_VALUE\",\n    73→        pkColumnValue=\"VENDOR_PART_ID\",\n    74→        allocationSize=10)\n    75→    @Id\n    76→    @GeneratedValue(strategy=GenerationType.TABLE, generator=\"vendorPartGen\")\n    77→    public Long getVendorPartNumber() {\n    78→        return vendorPartNumber;\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    public void setVendorPartNumber(Long vendorPartNumber) {\n    82→        this.vendorPartNumber = vendorPartNumber;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    public String getDescription() {\n    86→        return description;\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    public void setDescription(String description) {\n    90→        this.description = description;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    public double getPrice() {\n    94→        return price;\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    public void setPrice(double price) {\n    98→        this.price = price;\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    @OneToOne\n   102→    @JoinColumns({\n   103→        @JoinColumn(name=\"PARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName=\"PARTNUMBER\"),\n   104→        @JoinColumn(name=\"PARTREVISION\", referencedColumnName=\"REVISION\")\n   105→    })\n   106→    public Part getPart() {\n   107→        return part;\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    public void setPart(Part part) {\n   111→        this.part = part;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    @JoinColumn(name=\"VENDORID\")\n   115→    @ManyToOne\n   116→    public Vendor getVendor() {\n   117→        return vendor;\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public void setVendor(Vendor vendor) {\n   121→        this.vendor = vendor;\n   122→    }\n   123→\n   124→}\n   125→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"6864200c-5f73-47bf-8506-d182476fa7c6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01HodH12tS6Yt8d3mywsw8W5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`VendorPart.getVendorPartNumber()` returns a `Long` (auto-generated ID), not the description like \"PART1\". The description is in `getDescription()`. The original Quarkus app showed the same `vendorPartNumber` which is the auto-generated ID. That's the original behavior - so displaying 1, 2, 4 is correct (those are the generated IDs).\n\nNow let me also test CSS and other endpoints:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1750,"cache_read_input_tokens":87705,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1750,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":283},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e80e1467-8d50-4d14-a21d-b94c86ec6299","uuid":"c073e807-5543-4be5-82cd-af7d649dc3db"}
